Refactor the Harness struct to use the new type system with enhanced methods.

## Changes to HarnessKind

```rust
pub enum HarnessKind {
    ClaudeCode,
    OpenCode,
    Goose,
}

impl HarnessKind {
    /// All known harness types
    pub const ALL: &'static [HarnessKind] = &[
        HarnessKind::ClaudeCode,
        HarnessKind::OpenCode,
        HarnessKind::Goose,
    ];
}
```

## New Harness Struct

```rust
pub struct Harness {
    kind: HarnessKind,
}

impl Harness {
    pub fn new(kind: HarnessKind) -> Self;
    pub fn kind(&self) -> HarnessKind;

    /// Returns all harnesses installed on this system
    pub fn installed() -> Vec<Harness>;

    /// Check if this harness is installed
    pub fn is_installed(&self) -> bool;

    // Resource methods - all return Result<Option<_>>
    pub fn skills(&self, scope: &Scope) -> Result<Option<DirectoryResource>>;
    pub fn commands(&self, scope: &Scope) -> Result<Option<DirectoryResource>>;
    pub fn plugins(&self, scope: &Scope) -> Result<Option<DirectoryResource>>;
    pub fn mcp(&self, scope: &Scope) -> Result<Option<ConfigResource>>;
    pub fn rules(&self, scope: &Scope) -> Result<Option<DirectoryResource>>;
    pub fn agents(&self, scope: &Scope) -> Result<Option<DirectoryResource>>;
    pub fn config(&self, scope: &Scope) -> Result<PathBuf>;
}
```

## Error Handling Pattern
- Err(...) = system error (can't find home dir, etc.)
- Ok(None) = feature not supported by this harness
- Ok(Some(resource)) = supported, check resource.exists for presence

